title: List of keys

properties.name: description
properties.value: This is a list of the keys found in RuneScape in alphabetical order:

content:
The RuneScape Wiki also has an article on: rsw:List of keys
For other uses, see Key (disambiguation).

This is a list of the keys found in RuneScape in alphabetical order:

Key Uses
A small key Used during Plague City quest
Ancestral key[1] Used during Spirits of the Elid
Ancient key Used during Dragon Slayer II
Bakery storage key
Bank key Allows access to victim's bank in Deadman mode
Battered key[1] Used during Elemental Workshop I and Elemental Workshop II
Bedabin key Used during The Tourist Trap
Black key black Shades of Mort'ton
Black key brown Shades of Mort'ton
Black key crimson Shades of Mort'ton
Black key purple Shades of Mort'ton
Black key red Shades of Mort'ton
Bloodier key
Bloody key
Bluish key Used in A Kingdom Divided
Bone key (Ghosts Ahoy) Used in Ghosts Ahoy
Bone key (Shilo Village) Used in Shilo Village
Brass key[1] Grants access to the back door of Edgeville Dungeon
Brimstone key Used to open the Brimstone chest atop Mount Karuulm
Brittle key Grants permanent access to the Slayer Tower roof entrance
Bronze key (H.A.M.) Stolen from H.A.M. Guards to open chests
Bronze key (Monkey Madness II)
Bronze key (Prince Ali Rescue)
Bronze key (Recruitment Drive) Used during Recruitment Drive
Bronze key black Used to open the Shade Catacombs
Bronze key brown Used to open the Shade Catacombs
Bronze key crimson Used to open the Shade Catacombs
Bronze key purple Used to open the Shade Catacombs
Bronze key red Used to open the Shade Catacombs
Cavern key Used during Creature of Fenkenstrain
Cell door key Used during The Tourist Trap
Cell key 1 Used during Troll Stronghold
Cell key 2 Used during Troll Stronghold
Chest key (Digsite) Used during The Dig Site
Chest key (Ghosts Ahoy) Used during Ghosts Ahoy
Chest key (Hazeel Cult) Used during Hazeel Cult
Chest key (Pirate's Treasure) Used during Pirate's Treasure
Cold key Used in A Kingdom Divided
Combat damaged key
Crypt key Used in A Night at the Theatre
Crypt key (2018 Halloween event) Used in 2018 Halloween event
Crystal key Opens the crystal chest in Taverley
Crystal-mine key[1] Obtained after defeating Treus Dayth during Haunted Mine
Damp key Used in A Kingdom Divided
Dark key Opens the dark chest in the Crumbling Tower basement on the Isle of Souls
Display cabinet key Used during The Golem
Door key (Darkness of Hallowvale)
Door key (Witch's House) Used during Witch's House and Grim Tales
Dragon key Used during Dragon Slayer II
Dusty key[1] Used to open the gate to the blue dragons area in Taverley Dungeon
Ecumenical key Used to enter God Wars Dungeon boss rooms without the need for killcount. Can only be obtained by killing monsters within the Wilderness God Wars Dungeon
Emerald key
Enchanted key (item)[1] Used to find treasure after Making History
Enhanced crystal key Opens the elven crystal chest in Prifddinas
Frozen key (The Frozen Door) Used during The Frozen Door miniquest to open the frozen door
Frozen key (The Fremennik Trials) Used during The Fremennik Trials
Giant key Used to access Obor's lair in the Edgeville Dungeon
Glough's key Used during The Grand Tree
Goblin kitchen key Used during the Observatory Quest
Golden key Used during Priest in Peril
Grubby key Used to open the Grubby Chest in the Forthos Dungeon
Iron key (H.A.M.) Stolen from H.A.M. Guards to open chests
Iron key Used during Priest in Peril
Jail key Dropped by the jailer in the Black Knights' Base within the Taverley Dungeon
Key (Biohazard) Used during Biohazard
Key (Elemental Workshop II) Used during Elemental Workshop II
Key (Ernest the Chicken) Used during Ernest the Chicken
Key (Gnome Village Dungeon) Opens the door to the cell in which Golrie is contained in Tree Gnome Village dungeon.
Key (Melzar's Maze) Used during Dragon Slayer I
Key (Olaf's Quest) Used during Olaf's Quest
Key (The Lost Tribe) Used during The Lost Tribe
Key (Treasure Trails) Only obtained during treasure trails
Key (Waterfall Dungeon) Opens 2 doors in the Waterfall Dungeon.
Key (Witch's House) Used during Witch's House
Key master's key
Keys Used during The Feud
Large ornate key
Larran's key Used to open Larran's small and big chests in the wilderness
Lighthouse key Used during Horror from the Deep
Manor key
Maze key[1] Used during Dragon Slayer I
Metal key[1] Used during Tourist Trap
Miscellaneous key Used during Heroes' Quest
Mossy key Used to access to Bryophyta's lair
Muddy key Obtained as a drop from chaos dwarves. Opens the muddy chest
New key[1] Used during Mourning's End Part II
Ogre coffin key Obtained as drops from zogres and skogres. Opens an ogre coffin
Ogre gate key Used during Zogre Flesh Eaters
Old key
Prison key (Prison Pete) Given to Prison Pete to return to RuneScape
Prison key (Troll Stronghold) Used during Troll Stronghold
Prize key
Ruby key
Sapphire key
Seer's key Used during The Fremennik Trials
Shed key Used during Creature of Fenkenstrain
Shiny key[1] Used during Temple of Ikov
Silver key (H.A.M.) Stolen from H.A.M. Guards to open chests
Silver key black Reward from Shades of Mort'ton, opens black silver chest in Shade Catacombs
Silver key brown Reward from Shades of Mort'ton, opens brown silver chest in Shade Catacombs
Silver key crimson Reward from Shades of Mort'ton, opens crimson silver chest in Shade Catacombs
Silver key purple Reward from Shades of Mort'ton, opens purple silver chest in Shade Catacombs
Silver key red Reward from Shades of Mort'ton, opens red silver chest in Shade Catacombs
Silverlight key (Captain Rovin) Used during Demon Slayer
Silverlight key (Sir Prysin) Used during Demon Slayer
Silverlight key (Wizard Traiborn) Used during Demon Slayer
Sinister key Used to open the sinister chest in Yanille
Steel key (H.A.M.) Stolen from H.A.M. Guards to open chests
Steel key black Reward from Shades of Mort'ton, opens black steel chest in Shade Catacombs
Steel key brown Reward from Shades of Mort'ton, opens brown steel chest in Shade Catacombs
Steel key crimson Reward from Shades of Mort'ton, opens crimson steel chest in Shade Catacombs
Steel key purple Reward from Shades of Mort'ton, opens purple steel chest in Shade Catacombs
Steel key red Reward from Shades of Mort'ton, opens red steel chest in Shade Catacombs
Storeroom key Used in Eadgar's Ruse
Tarnished key Used in Mourning's End Part I, frees the gnome from prison
Temple key
Temple library key Used during In Aid of the Myreque
Toban's key Used during Watchtower
Tower key Used in Creature of Fenkenstrain, opens door to Lord Rologarth's tower
Useless key
Vault key
Warm key Found in the Smoke Dungeon, used to open Fareed's door
Weapon store key Used during Shield of Arrav. Can only be obtained if the player is in the Phoenix Gang
Wrought iron key[1] Used in Tourist Trap
Zealot's key Used during Haunted Mine
  1. ^ 1.00 1.01 1.02 1.03 1.04 1.05 1.06 1.07 1.08 1.09 1.10 These keys can be placed on the Steel key ring.
